now , of all the people i met , the blood i was from the sierra nevada de santa marta in northern colombia , the most extraordinary .
afterwards of the old tyrannical civilization , populating the caribbean coastal plain of colombia , and as a result of conquest , this people removed to an isolated volcanic solid that rises above the caribbean coastal plain .
in a bloodshed continent , these people were the only ones that were never conquered by the spain .
but to this day , they &apos;re governed by a ritual priesthood , but the training of the priesthood is very extraordinary .
the young acolyths are separated from their families at age three and four , and in a shadow world of eclipse , in stone huts at the age of the glacier for 18 years , and two periods of each nine years are deliberately chosen to mimic the nine months of pregnancy they spent in their light mother &apos;s lap , they now spend metamorphorphoric in the lap of the great mother .
and throughout that entire time , they &apos;re culturally introduced to the values of their society . values that sustain the claim that their prayers and only their prayers , the cosmic -- or we could say that ecological -- maintain equilibrium .
at the end of this amazing initiation , they &apos;re suddenly taken outside and for the first time in their lives , at the age of 18 , you see a sunrise . and in this crystal moment of consciousness , when the sun begins to shine on the hangs of the amazing beautiful landscape , suddenly everything they learned in the abstract world will be revealed in astonishing glory . and the priest will come back and say , &quot; see ? it &apos;s really how i told you .
it &apos;s so wonderful . you have to protect it . &quot;
they call themselves the older brothers and say that we are the younger brothers for the destruction of the world .
now this level of intuition becomes very important .
whenever we think about innate and landscape , we either call it rousseau and the old framework of the noble wild , which is , in its simplification , a racial thought or , on the other hand , thoreau and say , these people are more connected to nature than we are .
so , indigenous ones are not sentimental , nor are they elected by nostalgia .
there &apos;s not a lot of space in the malaria swamps of asmat or the cold winds of tibet , but they still , through time and ritual , shaped a mysterious nimbus of the earth that doesn &apos;t based on the idea of being aware of them , but on a much more subtle intuition , the idea that the earth can only exist because it &apos;s breathed into the human mind .
now , what does that mean ?
it means that a young child will grow up in the andean who &apos;s in the belief that the mountain is an apu spirit , who is his or her destiny , will become a very different person , and have a different relationship with this resource or this place than a little kid in montana , who grows up in thinking that a mountain is a bunch of stones that can be carried away .
whether it &apos;s a place of mind or a pile of heritage is irrelevant .
