and at the end of it , we &apos;re really faced with a choice . do we want to live in a monotonous world of monotonies or in a polychromatic world of diversity ?
margaret mead , the great anthropologist said before she died , that it &apos;s her greatest fear that as we move towards a thread , discretionary , generic view , we would see not only the entire range of human imagination reduced in a measured way of thinking , but that one day we wake up from a dream and forgot that there were ever other possibilities .
and it &apos;s humbling to think that our species may have existed for 600,000 years .
