that &apos;s a problem that many players have .
we think in reality , we &apos;re not as good as we are in games .
and i don &apos;t mean just less successful , even though that &apos;s part of it .
we &apos;re getting more in games . i mean , i &apos;m talking about the motivation of doing something significant , inspired to work together .
when we &apos;re in a game world , i think many of us are transformed into our best version at any given time and instant , trying to solve the problem intractable as long as it takes to try it after the failure again .
and in reality , when we fail , when we hit obstacles , we often feel different .
we feel overwhelmed . we feel defeated . we feel threatened , maybe depressed , frustrated or cynical .
we never have those feelings when we play games , in games they just don &apos;t exist .
